When it comes right down to it, national political conventions are televisi=
on shows, nothing more and nothing less. Sure, there are 20,000 people in t=
he hall, and the balloon drop is always a blast, but every one of the deleg=
ates and other grandees are already voting for Kamala Harris, so entertaini=
ng them only matters to the extent it makes the week of nightly broadcasts =
in primetime more riveting, highly rated, and successful in accomplishing o=
ther goals that are more tangible and measurable: reaching a bunch of peopl=
e who don=E2=80=99t normally pay attention to politics, raking in campaign =
contributions, and recruiting new foot soldiers to the cause. And it=E2=80=
=99s in terms of these quotidian metrics that the Democratic convocation in=
 Chicago last week was truly killer.

To give you a sense of how the political operative class assesses a
convention, consider this: When I sat down late Thursday night after Harris=
=E2=80=99s speech with Patrick Gaspard=E2=80=94Barack Obama=E2=80=99s forme=
r political director and ambassador to South Africa and now C.E.O. of the C=
enter for American Progress Action Fund=E2=80=94to tape the most recent epi=
sode of the Impolitic podcast, the first words out of his mouth had to do w=
ith volunteers. When Joe Biden was the party=E2=80=99s nominee, he noted, t=
he campaign had thousands of them; now it has hundreds of thousands. As Har=
ris campaign chair Jen O=E2=80=99Malley Dillon laid it out in an =E2=80=9Ci=
nterested parties=E2=80=9D memo a few days later: =E2=80=9CHeaded into the =
convention, our campaign hosted a weekend of action, and volunteers complet=
ed 10,000 shifts and contacted over 1 million voters. The convention itself=
 helped build on that momentum, generating nearly 200,000 new volunteer shi=
fts.=E2=80=9D

The other numbers coming out of the convention were just as striking.
Harris=E2=80=99s speech drew a whopping 28.9 million viewers, millions more=
 than Donald Trump=E2=80=99s rambling walk in the woods at the Republican c=
onvention last month. Over the weekend, Team K announced it had raised a st=
aggering $82 million last week, bringing the total it=E2=80=99s collected i=
n a little more than a month since KDH became the de facto nominee to $540 =
million, =E2=80=9Ca record for any campaign in history.=E2=80=9D

And yet, as Dan Pfeiffer wryly observed in his Message Box ( https://www.me=
ssageboxnews.com/p/why-you-shouldnt-panic-about-rfk?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best=
+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%288%2F25%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%=
