ss forced their guy out of the race. <br/><br/>A lot of attention was heape=
d on <b>Anita</b> <b>Dunn</b>=E2=80=99s comments at her farewell event sugg=
esting that <i>revenge</i> was a dish best served cold. She knew the commen=
ts were going to get out. And she=E2=80=99s since said she was trying to co=
unsel people in the White House that it=E2=80=99s a long game. Dunn wants t=
o prevent Trump from having a restoration as much as any Democrat in the co=
untry. And she likes Harris. <br/><br/>Now, that doesn=E2=80=99t take the e=
dge off her words. Dunn is a hardcore player, but she wasn=E2=80=99t announ=
cing her own personal retribution campaign to bring down the Harris ticket =
in the next 70 days. She was saying there were
people who were disloyal to Joe Biden and in the long run, they may pay a p=
rice for that. There are a lot of people there who are still seething and s=
immering over what happened. And, polls be damned, there=E2=80=99s no quest=
ion Biden still thinks he was going to beat Donald Trump in the fall. <br/>=
